.Dd March 28, 2026
.Dt KAT 1
.Os Kayako
.Sh NAME
.Nm kat
.Nd execute a command with Kernel Access Table privileges
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar command
.Op Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility executes the specified
.Ar command
with elevated privileges as defined in the Kernel Access Table (KAT).
Unlike sudo,
.Nm
does not necessarily grant full root access; it requests the kernel to 
apply specific privileges (e.g., system time adjustment) to the process 
based on the user's UID and the binary's path.
.Pp
The
.Nm
utility is a SetUID binary. It relies on the
.Nm kat.kmod
module being loaded and configured via
.Xr katadm 8 .
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Execute touch with the ability to modify root owned files:
.Pp
.Dl $ kat touch /test_file
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr katadm 8 ,
.Xr kauth 9
